The paper deals with convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and their compression, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of hash functions, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on several datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
